nl.tno.stormcv.model

Class CVParticle

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tno.stormcv.model.CVParticle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<CVParticle>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Descriptor, Feature, Frame, GroupOfFrames

    public abstract class CVParticle
extends Object
implements Comparable<CVParticle>
    An abstract Computer Vision Particle superclass which contains the information required for all objects processed by the platform:
    • streamId: an identifier of the stream a piece of information refers to
    • sequenceNr: the number within a stream a piece of information refers to (typically the frame number of a video stream/file)
    • metadata: Map<String,Object> that can be used to for other information
    Most of the standard components within StormCV make use of the streamId and sequenceNr to group, filter and order objects they get. CVParticles are compared based on their sequenceNr (ascending order).
    Author:
    Corne Versloot
